==English==

===Noun===
'''broadside'''

# {{nautical}} One [[side]] of a [[ship]] above the [[water]] [[line]]; all the [[gun]]s on one side of a [[warship]]; their [[simultaneous]] [[firing]].
# (''by extension'') A [[forceful]] [[verbal]] [[attack]].
# A large [[sheet]] of [[paper]], [[printed]] on one side and [[folded]].
# The [[printed]] [[lyrics]] of a [[folk song]] or [[ballad]]; a [[broadsheet]].

====Translations====
;one side of a warship
{{top}}
*Finnish: [[täyslaidallinen]], [[täysilaidallinen]]
{{bottom}}

===Adverb===
'''broadside'''

# [[sideways|Sideways]]; with the side [[turned]] to the [[direction]] of some [[object]].

===Verb===
'''to broadside'''

# {{transitive}} To [[collide]] with something sideways on

